doc.after: Started in June 2002, it reached one thousand article by May 2011.[3][7][8] As of January 2013, it has 3184 articles and got rank 161 according to article count.[9] Oriya Wikipedians have organized meetups and workshops in seven different cities like Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, Anugul, Balasore, Bangalore and New Delhi[10] across India.[11] The readership has increased over 300% in the last six months. The page views per month is at 4.84 lakh. This Wikipedia ranks 176 among the 286 world language Wikipedias.[12][13]
